第一题
one <- df1 %>% 
    mutate(industry = as.factor(industry)) %>% 
    group_by(industry) %>% 
    summarise(n = n())

one %>% 
    ggplot(aes(reorder(industry, n), n))+
    geom_point(shape = 17)+
    geom_line(aes(group = 1))+
    labs(x = "", y = "") +
    coord_flip()



第二题
two_1 <- df1 %>% 
    group_by(valuation) %>% 
    summarise(count = n())

two_1 %>% 
    ggplot()+
    geom_bar(aes(x = valuation, y = count), stat = "identity", col = "red")



第二题第二问
two_2 <- df1 %>% 
    arrange(-valuation) %>% 
    slice(4:n())

two_2 %>% 
    ggplot()+
    geom_point(aes(x = industry, y = valuation, col = -valuation, size = valuation))+
    theme(legend.position = "") +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45))+
    labs(title = "胡润大中华区独角兽企业估值")



第三题
three <- df1 %>% 
    mutate(sum = n()) %>% 
    group_by(headquarter, sum) %>% 
    summarise(n = n()) %>% 
    mutate(rate = n / sum) 

three %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = reorder(headquarter, n), y = rate))+
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", width = .1, fill = "lightblue")+
    geom_point(col = "navyblue") +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent, limits = c(0, 0.5), breaks = seq(0, 0.5, 0.2))+
    labs(x = "城市", y = "占比%")+
    coord_flip()



第三题第二问
three_2 <- df1 %>% 
    filter(headquarter %in% c("北京", "上海")) %>% 
    mutate(value = log2(valuation))

three_2 %>%     
    ggplot(aes(x = industry, y = value))+
    geom_jitter(aes(col = headquarter, fill = headquarter, size = valuation), 
                height = 3, width = 0.1, alpha = 0.7, show.legend = F)+
    scale_color_brewer(palette = "Set2")+
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45))+
    facet_wrap(~ headquarter, nrow = 2)



第四题
test <- df1$ranking_chg

test_1 <- sub(pattern = "\\↓", replacement = "-", x = test)

test_2 <- sub(pattern = "\\↑", replacement = "", x = test_1)
    

four <- df1 %>% 
    mutate(tmp1 = sub(pattern = "\\↓", replacement = "", x = ranking_chg)) %>% 
    mutate(tmp2 = if_else(tmp1 > 0, tmp1, NULL)) %>%
    mutate(tmp3 = sub(pattern = "\\↑", replacement = "", x = tmp1)) %>% 
    mutate(tmp4 = if_else(tmp3 > 0, tmp3, NULL))
    #view()
